text: General Muhammad Musa Khan Hazara (October 20, 1908 â€“ March 12, 1991) was a military personnel and politician in Pakistan. He was the fourth Commander in Chief of Pakistan Army from 1966 to 1969. He was the eldest son of Sardar Yazdan Khan, born in a Hazara family of Quetta, British India, in 1908.
